    public final class PieTimeChart<P extends PeriodSetPlot>
extends SetPeriodChart<P>
    PieTimeChart This is the PieChart equivalent of a TimeChart It plots the sum of quantities over a period and uses the same mapping classes the intention is that you can use this to generate piecharts and timecharts interchangably. Unlike TimeCharts only a single dataset is plotted. This defaults to the last created Plot but can be reset using the setPlot(PeriodSetPlot) method.
